<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,560,871]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Compared with 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[377,622,560,586]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[484,542,560,586]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(1966
</bibRefCitation>
: map 14), the distribution for this species has been extended in the eastern part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[407,467,596,622]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">DRC</collectingCountry>
into 
<collectingCountry box="[528,627,595,621]" name="Burundi" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Burundi</collectingCountry>
, and in the southwestern part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1052,1115,596,622]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">DRC</collectingCountry>
, but in the northwestern part of the country it seems to be lacking. The specimens from Boende seem a bit out of place, as 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas &amp; Henry" box="[189,569,666,693]" firstAuthor="Thomas" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="270 - 272" refId="ref273790" refString="Thomas D. &amp; Henry M. 2013 b. Micropteropus pusillus Peters's Lesser Epauletted Fruit Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 270 - 272. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="b">Thomas &amp; Henry (2013b: 271)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that it avoids the Congolian rainforest except around its edges. 
<bibRefCitation author="Monfort" box="[272,516,702,728]" firstAuthor="Monfort" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="141 - 151" refId="ref270472" refString="Monfort A. 1992. Premiere liste commentee des mammiferes du Rwanda. Revue de zoologie africaine 106 (2): 141 - 151." type="journal article" year="1992">Monfort (1992: 142)</bibRefCitation>
believes this species occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[890,989,702,728]" name="Rwanda" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
, based on a reference to “Ruanda- 
<collectingCountry box="[189,275,737,763]" name="Burundi" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Urundi</collectingCountry>
” by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schouteden" box="[332,556,737,764]" firstAuthor="Schouteden" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 576" refId="ref273033" refString="Schouteden H. 1947. De Zoogdieren van Belgisch Congo en van Ruanda-Urundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen (2), 3: 1 - 576." type="journal article" year="1947">Schouteden (1947)</bibRefCitation>
and the locality “Congo-Nil-Aka” mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[1253,1313,738,764]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 27
</bibRefCitation>
- RBINS 13522). Monfort claims this locality to refer to “Nil-Akagera”, which is in 
<collectingCountry box="[1250,1346,773,799]" name="Rwanda" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
and not in 
<collectingCountry box="[270,369,808,834]" name="Burundi" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Burundi</collectingCountry>
, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[432,740,808,835]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[542,603,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 81)
</bibRefCitation>
provide coordinates for “Congo-Nil-Akka”, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1283,1394,807,835]" degrees="04" direction="north" minutes="35" orientation="latitude" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" precision="925" value="4.5833335">04°35′ N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[189,293,842,871]" degrees="29" direction="east" minutes="45" orientation="longitude" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" precision="925" value="29.75">29°45′ E</geoCoordinate>
, which put it in the Garamba National Park on the border with 
<collectingCountry box="[1034,1187,844,870]" name="South Sudan" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">South Sudan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
